article.headline: Rhode Island 82, New Hampshire 53
article.story: SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Brian Woodward scored 23 points and Dawan Robinson added 22 on Sunday as Rhode Island won its fourth straight game, 82-53 over New Hampshire. Robinson scored nine points in a 16-3 first-half run that gave the Rams (7-2) a 38-23 lead. Dustin Hellenga was the playmaker, setting up Robinson and Scott Hazelton for the first two baskets of the run, then assisting Woodward for a 3-point play that made it 31-20 with 6:29 to go in the half. Hellenga finished with 10 assists. Hazelton, playing his first game for Rhode Island since transferring from Connecticut, scored 10 points. Rhode Island led 45-28 at halftime then extended the lead with a 14-2 run to start the second half, sparked by a pair of 3-pointers from Robinson. The largest Rhode Island lead was 82-49 in the final minute when Tyrese Sullivan hit a 3-pointer. Craig Walls had 10 points and 13 rebounds to lead New Hampshire (3-5).
